      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2011 BMW M3 (E92) powered by the high-revving S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This unit features the desirable 6-speed manual gearbox and the M Variable Differential Lock for optimal torque vectoring. The engine breathes through eight individual throttle bodies, delivering a linear power band up to its 8,400 RPM redline. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a recent rod bearing replacement with VAC coated shells and updated throttle valve actuators. The chassis retains its composure via Electronic Damper Control (EDC), though the exterior shows minor road-wear consistent with enthusiast use. This is a driver-focused example with a rigid subframe and a carbon fiber roof for a lower center of gravity.",
